To draw a chessboard using LATEX, you can use the `chessboard` package. Here's an example code that shows how to create a chessboard using this package:

```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
\begin{document}
\chessboard[black,boardwidth=100,boardheight=100,showpieces=false]{1}
\end{document}
```

In this code, we are using the `chessboard` package and specifying the color (black) and dimensions of the board. The `boardwidth` and `boardheight` options should be set to the desired size of the chessboard, in this example, I set it to 100 units. The `showpieces` option is set to `false` to avoid showing the pieces on the board. Finally, the `1` specifies the starting position (row 1 and column 1) for the black pieces.

To compile this code, you would need LATEX installed on your computer. Simply save the code in a LATEX file (e.g., `chessboard.tex`), open a terminal, navigate to the folder where the file is located, and run the following command:

```
latex chessboard.tex
dvips -Ppdf -o chessboard.pdf chessboard.dvi
```

This will compile the LATEX code and generate a PDF file named `chessboard.pdf`, which you can open in a PDF viewer to see the chessboard image.

